abstract: The gloom pervading the financial markets and the business climate has reached the land of innovation.
snippet: The gloom pervading the financial markets and the business climate has reached the land of innovation.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO  Housing prices in Silicon Valley remain defiantly high. New BMWs and Saabs cruise Highway 101. But for the first time there are signs that the current economic downturn is taking its toll on the country’s cradle of technology and innovation.

abstract: Nationsbanc Montgomery Securities plans to open office in Silicon Valley for about 40 of its investment bankers who focus on computer-related industries (S)
snippet: Nationsbanc Montgomery Securities plans to open office in Silicon Valley for about 40 of its investment bankers who focus on computer-related industries (S)
lead_paragraph: Nationsbanc Montgomery Securities, the investment banking arm of the BankAmerica Corporation, plans to open an office in Silicon Valley for about 40 of its investment bankers who focus on computer-related industries, its chief executive said. Lewis W. Coleman, the securities firm's chief executive, said the San Francisco-based company would keep its technology research operations and the rest of its business in San Francisco. It is opening a Silicon Valley office to be closer to some clients. Several investment banks have expanded in Silicon Valley, including Goldman, Sachs & Company, which announced a move there last month.

lead_paragraph: The technology industry is clearly prospering, but has it entered a period of irrational exuberance? There are good reasons to worry that it has and that the bursting of this bubble could be painful, to investors in and employees of tech firms as well as to the broader economy.
